WEBVTT

00:03.072 --> 00:06.247
Meredith: The idea that the
brain can convince the body

00:06.282 --> 00:08.422
that a fake treatment
is the real thing

00:08.456 --> 00:09.906
is called the placebo effect.

00:09.940 --> 00:12.426
♪ I could look into your eyes

00:12.460 --> 00:13.944
♪ Trace your shadows
in the way the sun moves ♪

00:13.979 --> 00:16.222
[ Gasps ]

00:16.257 --> 00:19.571
♪ Across the ocean and the sky

00:19.605 --> 00:20.917
♪ There's nothing better
than laying next to you ♪

00:20.951 --> 00:23.678
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

00:23.713 --> 00:27.372
♪ I love the way our bodies
set the scene ♪

00:27.406 --> 00:31.065
♪ Bathing in the colors
of a dream ♪

00:31.100 --> 00:32.756
♪ No one in the world,
just you and me ♪

00:32.791 --> 00:34.620
[ Chuckles ]

00:36.450 --> 00:38.417
[ Gasps ] No!

00:38.452 --> 00:40.074
[ Laughs ]

00:40.109 --> 00:43.250
♪ In the golden hour

00:43.284 --> 00:44.941
Hey.
I was never here.

00:44.975 --> 00:48.289
It's okay,
I'm not in my dress yet.

00:48.324 --> 00:49.980
Well, in that case...

00:51.948 --> 00:53.812
♪ You taste like honey butter

00:53.846 --> 00:55.469
♪ You're sugar sweet

00:55.503 --> 00:56.470
Enjoy your coffee.

00:56.504 --> 00:57.919
Thank you.
Love you.

00:57.954 --> 00:59.818
I love you.

00:59.852 --> 01:01.233
Bye.

01:01.268 --> 01:03.132
The brain anticipates
an outcome

01:03.166 --> 01:06.376
and then communicates it
to the body.

01:06.411 --> 01:10.277
♪ I love the way our bodies
set the scene ♪

01:10.311 --> 01:13.280
♪ Bathing in the colors
of a dream ♪

01:13.314 --> 01:17.663
♪ No one in the world,
just you and me ♪

01:19.838 --> 01:20.804
Lucas?

01:20.839 --> 01:22.461
♪ Meet me at sundown

01:22.496 --> 01:24.567
♪ In the golden hour

01:24.601 --> 01:29.295
And the body responds as if
a medication were given...

01:29.330 --> 01:32.368
when all that was given
was a sugar pill.

01:34.059 --> 01:37.856
Studies have found that
under the right circumstances,

01:37.890 --> 01:42.930
a placebo can have up
to a 72% cure rate --

01:42.964 --> 01:46.485
making it just as effective
as certain medications.

01:46.520 --> 01:48.625
So, the lie becomes the truth.

01:48.660 --> 01:49.799
Happy wedding day!

01:49.833 --> 01:51.490
I need a ride.Ooh. That's why I'm here.

01:51.525 --> 01:53.146
No, I need a ride
to the hospital.
Okay.

01:53.182 --> 01:55.011
Winston: Mr. Kramer needs
his pacing wires pulled

01:55.045 --> 01:56.702
and Ms. Watkins
is back in a-fib.

01:56.737 --> 01:58.152
Okay, great.

01:58.187 --> 02:00.050
I'll, uh, keep an eye
and start the amio.

02:00.085 --> 02:01.190
I really appreciate this,
Chief.

02:01.224 --> 02:02.639
Yeah, of course.

02:02.674 --> 02:05.194
Oh, uh, Paige Harper in 2404
is post op day 2

02:05.228 --> 02:06.643
from her CABG, so...

02:06.678 --> 02:08.680
I will check
the test tube output

02:08.714 --> 02:10.060
and see
if we can remove them.

02:10.095 --> 02:11.855
[ Groans softly ]
You alright?

02:11.890 --> 02:14.478
Yeah, I'm fine.
I just have a toothache.

02:14.513 --> 02:15.825
I don't have to go
to Boston if --

02:15.859 --> 02:17.620
Yes, you do have to go
to Boston.

02:17.654 --> 02:19.035
If you need to go
to the dentist --

02:19.069 --> 02:20.623
You are not missing
the awards ceremony

02:20.657 --> 02:21.624
so I can go
to the dentist.

02:21.658 --> 02:22.866
Alright, well, I'm saying,

02:22.901 --> 02:24.178
the whole cardio department
is a lot

02:24.213 --> 02:25.041
with a tooth ache
if you're not chief.

02:25.075 --> 02:26.491
But you are chief,

02:26.525 --> 02:28.389
so you're also overseeing
the whole hospital.

02:28.424 --> 02:30.079
And I am saying
you are nominated

02:30.115 --> 02:31.634
for a Catherine Fox Award

02:31.668 --> 02:34.740
and it's not every day
that our head of cardio

02:34.775 --> 02:37.191
is nominated
for a Catherine Fox Award.

02:37.226 --> 02:38.641
Head of cardio?

02:38.675 --> 02:40.677
Congratulations,
Dr. Ndugu.

02:40.712 --> 02:42.196
[ Chuckles ]Blue: Incredible.

02:42.231 --> 02:43.577
Congratulations,
Dr. Ndugu.

02:43.611 --> 02:46.406
Th-- Thank you, Chief Altman.
Thank you.

02:46.442 --> 02:47.581
Wow.You have earned it.

02:47.615 --> 02:49.238
And we are lucky
to have you.

02:49.272 --> 02:51.654
I am -- I'm thrilled.[ Elevator bell dings ]

02:51.688 --> 02:52.655
You won't regret this.

02:52.689 --> 02:54.103
I know I won't.

02:54.139 --> 02:56.106
Alright, now go,
before you miss your flight.

02:56.141 --> 02:57.763
Alright, yeah, yeah.Okay.

03:00.973 --> 03:02.043
I can skip
the wedding.

03:02.078 --> 03:03.424
No, don't skip
the wedding.

03:03.459 --> 03:05.426
But you probably should skip
the reception.

03:05.461 --> 03:07.497
[ Elevator bell dings ]You got it. I'll be back in
a couple of hours, tops.

03:07.532 --> 03:09.119
Great.
Thank you.

03:12.709 --> 03:14.124
Wow.

03:14.159 --> 03:17.783
You are a vision worthy
of a Renaissance faire.

03:17.818 --> 03:18.957
Well, this is
my Renn Faire dress.

03:18.991 --> 03:20.027
How did you know?

03:20.061 --> 03:21.028
How could I not?

03:21.062 --> 03:22.616
Is it bad?

03:22.650 --> 03:24.134
[ Chuckles ] No.I didn't have time
to go shopping.

03:24.169 --> 03:25.757
It's perfect.

03:25.791 --> 03:27.207
You look like a fairy

03:27.241 --> 03:30.969
who took a magical pill
and grew into human size.

03:31.003 --> 03:33.765
Jules, my chart says
the same thing it did

03:33.799 --> 03:35.353
when you looked
three minutes ago

03:35.387 --> 03:37.147
and also
five minutes ago.

03:37.182 --> 03:38.977
Mm-hmm.
Have you written
your toast?

03:39.011 --> 03:40.289
My what?
My toast?

03:40.323 --> 03:42.463
Well, you're
the maid of honor.

03:42.498 --> 03:44.120
Crap.

03:44.154 --> 03:47.227
Oh. Well, just smile
and say you've never seen

03:47.261 --> 03:50.299
two people so happy
and in love.

03:50.333 --> 03:51.886
That's it?

03:51.921 --> 03:55.096
All those awful jokes
about ex-lovers and bad choices?

03:55.131 --> 03:57.789
It's the strangest
wedding-day tradition.

03:57.823 --> 04:02.103
You be the Fairy of Love
and just let it die with you.

04:02.138 --> 04:04.140
Dr. Kwan your date?

04:04.174 --> 04:05.728
No.

04:05.762 --> 04:07.626
The Fairy
of Playing Hard to Get.

04:07.661 --> 04:09.007
Mm, I like it.

04:09.041 --> 04:10.974
I will see you
after the wedding.

04:11.009 --> 04:13.839
Ta ta, love!
Have fun.

04:13.874 --> 04:16.014
Sam Sutton, 43,
post op day 4.

04:16.048 --> 04:17.740
I'm sorry.
Do we have to do this?

04:17.774 --> 04:18.741
Do what?

04:18.774 --> 04:20.087
The whole formal thing?

04:20.120 --> 04:22.262
Post op day
blah, blah, blah.

04:22.296 --> 04:24.781
We practically live together.
Can we just be friends?

04:24.816 --> 04:26.852
Sam --
Mr. Sutton,
what's my name?

04:26.887 --> 04:27.853
Yasuda.

04:27.888 --> 04:29.441
What's my first name?

04:29.476 --> 04:30.925
Doctor?
Right.

04:30.960 --> 04:32.409
I am affable
and you are charming,

04:32.444 --> 04:34.101
but we're not friends,
Mr. Sutton.

04:34.135 --> 04:37.415
I am Dr. Yasuda,
and I am on your surgical team.

04:37.449 --> 04:38.830
I did eight years
of formal training

04:38.864 --> 04:40.694
to become a member
of your surgical team,

04:40.728 --> 04:43.041
so a formal introduction
of your medical status each day

04:43.075 --> 04:46.044
is not just appropriate,
it's one of the many systems

04:46.078 --> 04:48.702
that helps keep you
alive and safe.

04:48.736 --> 04:50.220
Alright?

04:50.255 --> 04:52.153
Mm-hmm.

04:52.188 --> 04:53.500
Alright, then.

04:53.534 --> 04:56.399
Sam Sutton, 43,
post op day 4.

04:59.091 --> 05:00.783
What are you doing here?
It's your wedding day.

05:00.817 --> 05:02.647
[ Sighs ]
Have you seen Adams?

05:02.681 --> 05:04.338
No.

05:08.687 --> 05:11.069
[ Breathing heavily ]

05:11.103 --> 05:12.691
You left without me.

05:14.866 --> 05:17.869
I didn't think
you were coming.

05:17.903 --> 05:20.975
Our breast cancer patient,
Tobey Barrett,

05:21.010 --> 05:22.632
is coming in
for her mastectomy today.

05:22.667 --> 05:23.806
Okay?

05:23.840 --> 05:25.394
I told her I'd be there
for her

05:25.428 --> 05:26.636
and I'd walk her through it
and I'd hold her hand,

05:26.671 --> 05:28.155
but they scheduled it
for today,

05:28.189 --> 05:29.363
and I don't want her
to put it off any longer,

05:29.398 --> 05:30.985
but I can't be here.You can't be here

05:31.020 --> 05:33.332
because you're
getting married today.

05:34.368 --> 05:37.060
I can't be here because
I'm getting married today.

05:39.408 --> 05:41.202
Lucas, um, I...

05:42.376 --> 05:45.310
I can't deny
what you feel.

05:46.449 --> 05:50.108
I can't deny that...
we have a connection.

05:50.142 --> 05:52.904
But Trey does love me,

05:52.938 --> 05:56.701
and I think what he and I built
together deserves this chance.

05:56.735 --> 05:59.945
And...

05:59.980 --> 06:00.946
I don't want
to hurt you,

06:00.981 --> 06:05.779
and I don't want
to lose you...

06:05.813 --> 06:07.574
from my life.

06:09.921 --> 06:12.199
But I'm getting married.

06:12.233 --> 06:14.408
Today.

06:14.443 --> 06:18.654
So, will you please...

06:20.241 --> 06:22.105
...take care
of Tobey for me?

06:24.004 --> 06:25.523
I'd do anything for you.

06:25.557 --> 06:31.563
♪♪

06:33.082 --> 06:34.739
Excellent work,
Yasuda.

06:34.773 --> 06:36.223
That guy needs
a little humbling.

06:36.257 --> 06:37.638
Agree. Thank you.

06:37.673 --> 06:40.296
And, uh, if he's ever
inappropriate with you

06:40.330 --> 06:42.229
in any way --
Oh, he's not
inappropriate

06:42.263 --> 06:44.404
unless by "inappropriate,"
you mean arrogant.

06:44.438 --> 06:45.784
Okay, Yasuda,
let's order a CT angio.

06:45.819 --> 06:47.165
I'm a bit concerned

06:47.199 --> 06:48.787
about decreased pulses
in his left arm.

06:48.822 --> 06:50.617
I'll talk to radiology,
but as a reminder,

06:50.651 --> 06:52.653
I have a wedding to get to
for the next few hours.

06:52.688 --> 06:54.137
I know
we're short-staffed today,

06:54.172 --> 06:56.312
so I wanted to get here
to be here for rounds,

06:56.346 --> 06:58.659
but it is
Dr. Griffith's wedding.

06:58.694 --> 07:00.799
Hmm, well,
we'll cover for you.Thank you.

07:00.834 --> 07:03.940
Yasuda, you don't think
he's inappropriate with...

07:03.975 --> 07:05.252
anyone?

07:05.286 --> 07:07.461
If you mean Dr. Wilson,
respectfully,

07:07.496 --> 07:10.464
the inappropriate
seems to be reciprocal.

07:13.191 --> 07:15.124
[ Clears throat ]

07:15.158 --> 07:16.988
Hey, I can take
over his care if --

07:17.022 --> 07:18.196
Oh, no, no.

07:18.230 --> 07:19.991
Uh, let's get
his angio.

07:20.025 --> 07:21.164
Okay. Yeah.

07:25.617 --> 07:27.205
What are you doing here?No time
to answer that.

07:27.239 --> 07:28.482
See you
at the wedding!

07:29.483 --> 07:31.485
[ Shouting in Spanish ]

07:36.317 --> 07:37.836
W-What's his name?
Uh... ¿Cómo se llama?

07:37.871 --> 07:39.355
Enzo.
Enzo!

07:39.389 --> 07:40.356
Enzo!

07:45.223 --> 07:46.258
We need to go.
We need to go.

07:48.398 --> 07:52.057
♪♪

07:52.092 --> 07:53.990
I need some help here!

07:54.025 --> 07:56.717
I have what looks like an opiate
poisoning in an 8-year-old!

07:56.752 --> 08:00.031
Somebody page Dr. Hunt!

08:00.065 --> 08:03.172
--Captions by VITAC--

08:19.706 --> 08:21.017
Okay, keep up the 02.

08:21.052 --> 08:22.640
Glucose level is normal.

08:22.674 --> 08:24.504
Naloxone's in.Look, he presented textbook.

08:24.538 --> 08:26.540
I-I might be wrong.
Maybe it's not drug-related.

08:26.575 --> 08:27.645
[ Gasps ][ Gasps ]

08:27.679 --> 08:29.992
Owen: There's our answer.

08:30.026 --> 08:31.649
Kwan, you saved
this kid's life.

08:31.683 --> 08:33.650
Let's get a tox screen
and some activated charcoal,

08:33.684 --> 08:35.515
1 gram per kilogram, ASAP.

08:40.865 --> 08:42.522
Nice work.

08:42.556 --> 08:44.420
Once you get those labs,
call Child Protective Services.

08:44.454 --> 08:45.939
Really?

08:45.973 --> 08:47.561
She seems
pretty terrified.Doesn't matter.

08:47.596 --> 08:49.459
That's not up to us to figure
out how this kid OD'ed,

08:49.494 --> 08:51.772
but somebody has to,
okay?

08:51.807 --> 08:53.015
Help!

08:53.049 --> 08:54.292
Okay, let's get
another gurney

08:54.326 --> 08:55.811
and get a tox screen
for her, as well.

08:57.329 --> 08:59.366
This van is everything.

08:59.400 --> 09:01.264
I know.
[ Chuckles ]
How did you --

09:01.299 --> 09:04.716
I bought a piece of crap
and I made it everything,

09:04.751 --> 09:06.235
and it might be
my most proud thing.

09:06.269 --> 09:07.581
Except for what I did
this morning.

09:07.616 --> 09:08.858
What did you do
this morning?

09:08.893 --> 09:10.101
I showed my
attending surgeons --

09:10.135 --> 09:11.896
hell, I showed myself
who I can be

09:11.930 --> 09:14.450
when I'm not working three jobs
and buried in debt.

09:14.484 --> 09:17.073
I slept eight full hours
three nights in a row,

09:17.108 --> 09:19.559
and I-I feel
like a superhero

09:19.593 --> 09:22.492
who has unknowingly had
kryptonite in my shoe for years.

09:22.527 --> 09:25.254
And then someone took it out,
and I can freaking fly.

09:25.288 --> 09:26.807
[ Laughs ]
And, I mean,

09:26.842 --> 09:28.740
okay, yeah, I resented
the hell out of it,

09:28.775 --> 09:31.398
but you took
a stand for me, Taryn.

09:31.432 --> 09:33.262
It was you.

09:33.296 --> 09:35.575
You took
the kryptonite out.

09:35.609 --> 09:37.646
Can I kiss you
at this red light?

09:37.680 --> 09:39.061
[ Tires screech ]

09:39.095 --> 09:40.580
Totally.

09:40.614 --> 09:41.615
Come here.

09:41.650 --> 09:48.415
♪♪

09:48.449 --> 09:49.934
Tobey, right?

09:49.968 --> 09:51.176
Yes. Hi.

09:51.211 --> 09:53.627
Hey, Dr...

09:53.662 --> 09:54.628
Adams.

09:54.663 --> 09:56.596
Sorry, right.
[ Chuckles ]

09:56.630 --> 09:58.356
My memory is shot
when I'm nervous.

09:58.390 --> 09:59.771
It's alright.
Yeah.

09:59.806 --> 10:01.601
Have you seen
Dr. Griffith?

10:01.635 --> 10:02.809
She said
that she would be --

10:02.843 --> 10:04.120
Yeah,
she's getting married.

10:04.155 --> 10:05.915
Yeah, I know.

10:05.950 --> 10:07.089
She showed me her ring and --
and a picture of the dress.

10:07.123 --> 10:08.746
No, I mean she's
getting married today.

10:08.780 --> 10:10.333
So she's not here.
Oh.

10:10.368 --> 10:11.956
And she didn't
tell you because...

10:11.990 --> 10:13.923
Because she didn't
want me to postpone.

10:13.958 --> 10:14.924
Yeah.

10:14.959 --> 10:16.926
Because cancer.

10:16.961 --> 10:17.927
Yeah.

10:17.962 --> 10:19.446
Okay.

10:19.480 --> 10:20.930
Yeah, she's sorry.

10:20.965 --> 10:23.381
But, uh, she knows everything
is gonna be just fine,

10:23.415 --> 10:25.452
and she asked me
to stand in, so...

10:25.486 --> 10:26.453
[ Chuckles ]

10:26.487 --> 10:28.628
Well, did she elope?
No.

10:28.662 --> 10:31.216
But she said that you were
her man of honor.

10:31.251 --> 10:33.287
That is a thing
that changed.

10:33.322 --> 10:36.670
Oh, so you're not even
going to the wedding.

10:36.705 --> 10:39.190
She, uh...

10:39.224 --> 10:41.157
She asked me
to be here for you.

10:41.192 --> 10:42.780
Oh, okay.

10:42.814 --> 10:44.229
Are you all checked in?

10:44.264 --> 10:46.059
Is she good?Nurse:
Yes, she's all set.

10:46.093 --> 10:47.232
I'll show you to pre-op.

10:47.267 --> 10:48.682
Well, you know,
you don't have to --

10:48.717 --> 10:52.065
I promised Simone
I would be here for you.

10:53.100 --> 10:54.343
Okay.

10:56.034 --> 10:57.587
Thank you.

10:57.622 --> 11:03.628
♪♪

11:05.354 --> 11:07.321
[ Elevator bell dings ]If everything looks good,
then you'll soon be

11:07.356 --> 11:08.875
on your way
to do physical therapy

11:08.909 --> 11:11.325
in the hospital gym
instead of just your room.

11:11.360 --> 11:13.603
Finally.
Something dangerous.

11:13.638 --> 11:16.330
Hi, how are you
feeling today?

11:16.365 --> 11:22.820
I'm learning ASL, so I'm trying
to practice any chance I get.

11:22.854 --> 11:25.823
Do you know you just signed
"poop" and not "practice"?

11:25.857 --> 11:27.169
Basically you just said,

11:27.203 --> 11:29.171
"I'm trying to poop
any chance I get."

11:29.205 --> 11:30.275
No!
Yep.

11:30.310 --> 11:31.725
I picked it up overseas

11:31.760 --> 11:33.762
when I was evacuating
civilian refugees.

11:33.796 --> 11:35.902
ASL "Sesame Street" just seemed
to calm the kids down,

11:35.936 --> 11:38.111
so I caught the basics.Of course you did.

11:38.145 --> 11:40.458
But I only know the level
of a 4-year-old.
Mm.

11:40.492 --> 11:43.944
One through 10, colors,
farm animals...

11:43.979 --> 11:44.945
poop.

11:44.980 --> 11:46.050
[ Laughs ]

11:46.084 --> 11:47.776
Well,
CT's expecting us.

11:47.810 --> 11:49.225
We gotta go.
Okay.

11:50.640 --> 11:51.780
I'll come.

11:51.814 --> 11:53.298
Convenient.
And great!

11:53.333 --> 11:55.922
Because you are, in fact,
on Sam's surgical team.

11:55.956 --> 11:57.647
Mm-hmm.
Shall we?

11:57.682 --> 11:59.408
Mika:
It looks so pretty.

11:59.442 --> 12:01.479
Oh, we should put our gifts
over here.

12:01.513 --> 12:03.067
Trey: Hey.

12:03.101 --> 12:04.654
Hey, hey.
Hey.

12:04.689 --> 12:05.897
Florist didn't show up.
They had the wrong date.

12:05.932 --> 12:07.381
And it's my fault

12:07.416 --> 12:08.762
because I was supposed to be
doing the flowers.

12:08.797 --> 12:09.970
But they had this day
but the next month.

12:10.005 --> 12:11.282
I mean, do I tell her?

12:11.316 --> 12:12.628
She's in her room
trying on the dress

12:12.662 --> 12:14.285
and I'm not supposed to see her,
but there's no bouquet.

12:14.319 --> 12:16.287
So do I go tell her
and say she won't --Hey, take a breath.

12:16.321 --> 12:18.876
Deep breath. Ready?[ Inhales, exhales deeply ]

12:18.910 --> 12:21.948
You look very handsome
and the food looks great

12:21.982 --> 12:23.466
and everyone looks happy,

12:23.501 --> 12:25.779
and hey, I will go get
a bouquet for Simone.

12:25.814 --> 12:27.125
Alright, well,
she ordered tulips, okay?

12:27.160 --> 12:28.644
Those are
her mom's favorite.

12:28.678 --> 12:30.784
I can't promise tulips,
but I'll -- I'll do my best.

12:30.819 --> 12:33.476
Well, also, the altar and the
aisle could use some flowers.

12:33.511 --> 12:34.961
I paid for
a lot of flowers, though.

12:34.995 --> 12:36.686
Um, in college, I worked
in the floral section

12:36.721 --> 12:38.067
of the grocery store
for three weeks

12:38.102 --> 12:39.586
before I was moved
to the bakery,

12:39.620 --> 12:41.830
and I kind of have a gift
for shapes and colors.

12:41.864 --> 12:43.176
Oh, yeah?Yeah.

12:43.210 --> 12:44.246
Well, I'm really good
with my hands.

12:44.280 --> 12:45.765
[ Both laugh ]

12:45.799 --> 12:47.525
We're dates.We're dates.

12:47.559 --> 12:49.699
Thank you.
And thank you.

12:49.734 --> 12:51.425
Of course.

12:51.460 --> 12:57.638
So, can I kiss you again,
right now?

12:57.673 --> 12:59.295
Totally.

13:10.548 --> 13:11.825
Good morning.

13:11.860 --> 13:13.551
Good morning. Good morning.
Hello. Good morning.

13:13.585 --> 13:14.552
Winston: Hey, Marsh.
Hey.

13:14.586 --> 13:16.312
Alright, Ms. Selkie,

13:16.347 --> 13:19.281
so these are not just surgeons
from my flagship hospital,

13:19.315 --> 13:20.800
they are nominees.

13:20.834 --> 13:22.663
So, give them any and everything
that they want.

13:22.698 --> 13:25.218
But first, I want
a vodka martini in a glass.

13:25.252 --> 13:26.564
[ Chuckles ]

13:26.598 --> 13:28.669
Can I have a club soda
with ice, please?

13:28.704 --> 13:30.119
Thank you.

13:30.154 --> 13:31.362
Dr. Bailey.Bailey:
Hey, good morning.

13:31.396 --> 13:32.950
Hey, good morning.
Good morning.

13:32.984 --> 13:34.123
Um, where's, uh, Ben?

13:34.158 --> 13:35.711
Oh, uh, he stayed

13:35.745 --> 13:37.817
in case they need more hands
at the collapse site.

13:37.851 --> 13:40.336
I appreciate you, uh, saving me
a seat last minute.

13:40.371 --> 13:41.717
Good morning.How are you?

13:41.751 --> 13:43.132
Please, I don't know why
you didn't decide

13:43.167 --> 13:44.824
to go with us
from the start.

13:44.858 --> 13:48.517
Ugh, well, private jets produce
5 to 14 times more pollution

13:48.551 --> 13:50.830
per passenger
than commercial flights.

13:50.864 --> 13:52.832
Our planet is boiling.

13:52.866 --> 13:54.350
Also, they terrify me.

13:54.385 --> 13:57.181
Uh, can I get
a bourbon, neat?

13:57.215 --> 13:58.492
Thank you.
Here?

13:58.527 --> 14:00.149
Okay.
Yes.

14:00.184 --> 14:02.082
Dr. Marsh.
Yeah?

14:02.117 --> 14:04.429
I'm really happy you decided
to come with us.

14:04.464 --> 14:06.362
I also appreciate the ride.
Thank you.

14:06.397 --> 14:07.881
Yes.
Absolutely.

14:07.916 --> 14:09.918
[ Sighs ]
[ Laughs ]

14:09.952 --> 14:13.093
Uh, um, you're, uh,
in her seat.

14:13.128 --> 14:14.715
Right.
Excuse me.

14:14.750 --> 14:15.855
My bad.

14:15.889 --> 14:17.235
[ Laughs ]

14:19.099 --> 14:20.135
Oh.

14:22.033 --> 14:24.415
Well, at least you know
I won't get obnoxiously drunk

14:24.449 --> 14:27.004
and talk your ear off
for five hours. [ Chuckles ]

14:27.038 --> 14:28.626
Hey, Marsh.
Trade seats with me, man.

14:28.660 --> 14:30.248
Yeah. Sure.

14:31.491 --> 14:33.527
Thank you.
[ Clears throat ]

14:33.562 --> 14:35.702
Why do I get the feeling
this is gonna be a long flight?

14:35.736 --> 14:38.636
Excuse me,
can I get a bourbon?

14:38.670 --> 14:39.671
Uh, double.

14:47.438 --> 14:49.302
I'm just here to ask you
a couple questions.

14:49.336 --> 14:50.855
Is that okay?
Preguntas.

15:00.692 --> 15:03.764
Ms. Alvarez, I'd like to know
everything that happened today.

15:03.799 --> 15:05.387
Todo.

15:05.421 --> 15:06.595
I-I can see if I can
stick around

15:06.629 --> 15:08.493
if you need help
interpreting or --

15:08.528 --> 15:10.323
Someone should be
on their way down.

15:25.648 --> 15:26.960
Her EKG's negative.

15:26.995 --> 15:28.237
It seems that her collapse
might have been

15:28.272 --> 15:30.067
a vasovagal response
from the stress.

15:30.101 --> 15:32.172
Enzo's tox screen
came back clean.

15:32.207 --> 15:34.105
Okay, so I was wrong?

15:34.140 --> 15:35.624
I don't think you were.

15:35.658 --> 15:37.626
Fentanyl doesn't show up
on standard tox screens

15:37.660 --> 15:39.145
because it is synthetic.

15:39.179 --> 15:41.768
I asked them to test Enzo
for that specifically.

15:41.802 --> 15:43.321
Teddy: Hey.

15:43.356 --> 15:44.944
I, uh -- I thought you were
going to the wedding.

15:44.978 --> 15:46.531
I'm where I need to be.

15:46.566 --> 15:49.603
PICU's full, but the ICU
overflow can take him.

15:49.638 --> 15:50.846
Kwan?Okay.

15:50.880 --> 15:53.642
[ Sighs ]

15:53.676 --> 15:55.471
You okay?
Yeah, kinda.

15:55.506 --> 15:57.542
I'm just -- I'm being asked
to be in four different places.

15:57.577 --> 15:59.613
One is a cardio consult
upstairs.

15:59.648 --> 16:01.305
Go. I've got things
covered down here.

16:01.339 --> 16:02.720
Thanks.

16:02.754 --> 16:04.308
[ Clears throat ]
You need a dentist.

16:04.342 --> 16:07.138
I need a shot of tequila,
a string, and a door.

16:07.173 --> 16:08.829
We're not
in the Army anymore!

16:08.864 --> 16:11.487
Yeah, but that was a crazy day,
though, right?

16:12.695 --> 16:14.145
We just published
the results

16:14.180 --> 16:15.836
from Hamilton's
12-month follow-up,

16:15.871 --> 16:18.494
and he still hasn't had to
increase his dopamine therapy.

16:19.495 --> 16:21.118
Yeah, you, uh -- you --
you mentioned that.

16:21.152 --> 16:24.293
We also haven't observed any
negative neurological effects.

16:24.328 --> 16:26.640
I cannot wait
to tell Meredith.

16:26.675 --> 16:28.711
I'm sure
she'll be thrilled.

16:28.746 --> 16:30.990
You made her really happy.
You know that, right?

16:33.026 --> 16:35.546
Well, if that's true, she had
a very funny way of showing it.

16:35.580 --> 16:38.859
Well, Meredith has a funny way
of showing a lot of things.

16:40.275 --> 16:43.002
But now that she and the kids
are pretty settled,

16:43.036 --> 16:44.796
her mind may be open.

16:46.764 --> 16:48.317
Open to what?

16:48.352 --> 16:49.905
She asks about you.

16:49.939 --> 16:51.562
[ Laughs ] Wow.

16:51.596 --> 16:54.323
You really enjoy interfering
in other people's relationships.

16:54.358 --> 16:57.223
Uh, yeah, Meredith and I
are no longer in a relationship.

16:57.257 --> 16:58.776
You don't have feelings
for her anymore?

16:58.810 --> 17:00.329
Good God,
why do you care so much?

17:00.364 --> 17:02.366
Look, I-I've learned
with Meredith Grey that --

17:02.400 --> 17:03.712
that the more you chase her,

17:03.746 --> 17:05.438
the faster and farther
she will run.

17:05.472 --> 17:07.612
[ Chuckles ]
It's kind of perfect.

17:07.646 --> 17:09.200
What is?

17:09.234 --> 17:12.065
All three sisters,
single at the same time.

17:13.066 --> 17:15.586
Nope. [ Grunts ]

17:16.414 --> 17:19.555
[ Thudding ]Mm! It's okay.

17:19.589 --> 17:21.902
It's -- It's just mild
turbulence, Bailey.

17:21.936 --> 17:23.352
Not back there.

17:23.387 --> 17:24.871
Someone's this close
to getting thrown out

17:24.905 --> 17:26.976
of the emergency exit,
and it's not gonna be me.

17:27.011 --> 17:28.909
I've had a hard enough year.

17:28.944 --> 17:30.532
Hell, it was just
starting to get good.

17:30.566 --> 17:32.741
[ Chuckles ]

17:32.775 --> 17:35.192
What?
I can't watch the show?

17:35.226 --> 17:39.299
♪♪

17:39.334 --> 17:41.646
[ Sighs ]

17:43.786 --> 17:45.133
Are you okay?

17:45.167 --> 17:46.548
Yeah.

17:46.582 --> 17:48.791
I just...miss my mom.

17:48.826 --> 17:52.071
I mean, I obviously
never knew her, but...

17:52.105 --> 17:54.280
when I went on my first date
with Trey,

17:54.314 --> 17:57.076
a red robin perched on a tree
branch three feet away from us.

17:57.110 --> 17:58.560
Robins were my mother's
favorite bird.

17:58.594 --> 18:02.150
She collected them on mugs
and coasters and trinkets,

18:02.184 --> 18:05.808
so I took it as a sign
she was with me that day

18:05.843 --> 18:07.224
and Trey's
a good man.

18:07.258 --> 18:08.225
He's good.

18:08.259 --> 18:10.019
He's kind and...

18:11.780 --> 18:13.678
...he's steady and...

18:13.713 --> 18:15.232
he loves me,

18:15.266 --> 18:18.166
and I know that's what my mother
would have wanted...for me.

18:18.200 --> 18:20.168
She would have wanted me to have
what she had with my father.

18:20.202 --> 18:21.341
So...

18:24.206 --> 18:25.966
I miss her.

18:26.001 --> 18:28.314
I think she'd be proud
of me today.

18:29.487 --> 18:31.006
[ Knock on door ]

18:32.387 --> 18:33.353
Hi, Daddy.

18:33.388 --> 18:35.148
Simone.

18:36.184 --> 18:38.151
[ Chuckles ]

18:38.186 --> 18:39.463
Oh.

18:40.395 --> 18:42.293
[ Laughs ]

18:42.328 --> 18:44.157
You take
my breath away.

18:45.193 --> 18:47.850
[ Sighs, laughs ]

18:47.885 --> 18:49.611
I'm sorry.

18:49.645 --> 18:52.027
Um, Dewayne Griffith,
Simone's father.

18:52.061 --> 18:53.960
Jules Millin.
Maid of honor.

18:53.994 --> 18:55.513
[ Thud ]

18:55.548 --> 18:57.584
What was that?
[ Chuckles ]

19:00.587 --> 19:02.451
It's a bird.

19:02.486 --> 19:04.039
Is it okay?

19:04.073 --> 19:05.523
It is not.

19:06.524 --> 19:08.216
What kind of bird?

19:08.250 --> 19:10.735
Oh, you know, it's --
it's just, um...

19:12.703 --> 19:14.083
Oh, my God.
What just happened?

19:15.050 --> 19:16.327
Um...

19:16.362 --> 19:18.157
I'll get your grandmother's
sewing kit.

19:19.192 --> 19:20.228
It's fine.
I can -- I can sew.

19:20.262 --> 19:22.161
I can fix it.
Two minutes.

19:22.195 --> 19:23.231
Two...

19:23.265 --> 19:26.510
[ Breathing deeply ]

19:29.547 --> 19:30.824
Uh, you okay?

19:30.859 --> 19:32.585
Yes. Yes, yes.

19:32.619 --> 19:34.690
I'm just -- I'm just trying
to regulate my nervous system.

19:34.725 --> 19:36.002
By hyperventilating?

19:36.036 --> 19:37.176
It's a whole thing.

19:37.210 --> 19:38.522
Do you have an update?Uh, yeah.

19:38.556 --> 19:40.524
Dr. Robinson is still
in his previous surgery,

19:40.558 --> 19:42.526
so it'll still be
a while.

19:43.975 --> 19:46.046
[ Exhales deeply ]

19:47.082 --> 19:49.774
I wish I would have taken
the girls on one last ride.

19:49.809 --> 19:51.190
The girls?

19:51.224 --> 19:52.605
Oh.

19:52.639 --> 19:54.227
I just feel like I didn't
appreciate them

19:54.262 --> 19:55.746
while I had them.

19:55.780 --> 19:57.506
Uh, and you'll have plenty
of time to appreciate

19:57.541 --> 19:59.405
all the things
you want to appreciate.

19:59.439 --> 20:01.510
This surgery
is saving your life.
Right.

20:01.545 --> 20:04.133
And they'll do the
reconstruction later today --I know. I know.

20:04.168 --> 20:06.515
It's just they won't be
the same.

20:06.550 --> 20:07.999
They won't be the same.

20:09.967 --> 20:11.934
Because they'll be
cancer-free.

20:13.177 --> 20:14.868
[ Laughs ]

20:14.903 --> 20:16.215
Wow.

20:16.249 --> 20:19.218
Cute, a doctor,

20:19.252 --> 20:22.117
and somehow knows
the exact right thing to say.

20:22.151 --> 20:23.808
[ Sighs ]

20:23.843 --> 20:27.260
So, why didn't you go
to the wedding?

20:29.676 --> 20:30.953
Oh, damn.

20:30.988 --> 20:33.922
Man of honor,
skipping the wedding.

20:33.956 --> 20:35.613
You got it bad, huh?

20:35.648 --> 20:37.097
So bad.

20:37.132 --> 20:38.789
You want to hyperventilate
with me?

20:38.823 --> 20:40.100
Does it really work?

20:40.135 --> 20:41.481
Yeah.

20:42.482 --> 20:45.485
[ Breathes deeply ]

20:51.664 --> 20:52.630
Hey.

20:52.665 --> 20:53.631
Oh.
[ Clears throat ]

20:53.666 --> 20:55.150
Sam Sutton.

20:55.184 --> 20:57.842
Just had his follow-up CT angio,
post op day 4.

20:57.877 --> 20:59.292
This is the wingsuiter,
right?

20:59.327 --> 21:00.466
Yeah.
Mm-hmm.

21:00.500 --> 21:02.399
Alright, let me take a look.
Um...

21:02.433 --> 21:05.402
Yeah, he's got a grade 1
aortic transection.

21:05.436 --> 21:07.404
I mean,
see this small line?

21:07.438 --> 21:09.958
It's most likely
from a deceleration injury

21:09.992 --> 21:10.959
from the crash.

21:10.993 --> 21:11.925
How are his pressures?

21:11.960 --> 21:13.272
Good.
Good.

21:13.306 --> 21:15.757
But his prognosis is --
is favorable, right?

21:15.791 --> 21:18.138
Yeah, it should be good.
They usually heal on their own.

21:18.173 --> 21:20.175
But you need to keep
a watchful eye on him

21:20.209 --> 21:22.626
and re-scan him
48 hours from now.

21:22.660 --> 21:23.627
Got it.I'll take care of it.

21:23.661 --> 21:24.973
An intern
can manage it.

21:25.007 --> 21:26.319
Well, they're
at Griffith's wedding,

21:26.354 --> 21:27.527
so I can just check
between patients.

21:27.562 --> 21:28.666
Not necessary.
I'm his doctor.

21:28.701 --> 21:29.943
I don't mind.
Neither do I.

21:29.978 --> 21:31.428
You don't even
like him.

21:31.462 --> 21:33.533
Well,
not the way you do.

21:34.707 --> 21:36.605
Woman over PA:
Dr. Anderson to Orthopedics.

21:36.640 --> 21:39.194
Dr. Doug Anderson
to Orthopedics.

21:39.228 --> 21:41.127
Give me a second.

21:41.161 --> 21:42.887
Maxine?
Everything okay?

21:42.922 --> 21:45.165
Oh! Oh, Dr. Kwan!
Thank heavens.

21:45.200 --> 21:47.236
I'm all turned around.

21:47.271 --> 21:49.273
C-Can you tell me
what day it is?

21:50.378 --> 21:52.345
The last time we found you
wandering the halls,

21:52.380 --> 21:54.071
you were septic
and delirious.

21:54.105 --> 21:55.383
It's Friday.

21:55.417 --> 21:57.385
I'm at Grey-Sloan Memorial,

21:57.419 --> 22:00.836
and can you please explain
why there's someone in my room?

22:02.424 --> 22:04.806
Your room is
on the north side.

22:04.840 --> 22:06.083
This is the south.

22:06.117 --> 22:08.396
[ Chuckling ]Enzo: Mom?

22:08.430 --> 22:09.983
Oh, okay.

22:10.018 --> 22:11.571
Do you know
where my mama is?

22:11.606 --> 22:13.884
She'll be back as soon
as she can, alright?

22:13.918 --> 22:15.817
[ Cellphone chimes ]

22:15.851 --> 22:16.990
[ Sighs ]

22:17.025 --> 22:18.337
I just got called in
for a consult.

22:18.371 --> 22:20.822
Well, you go.
I-I'll sit with him.

22:20.856 --> 22:22.271
No, you need to get
back in bed.

22:22.306 --> 22:25.516
Oh, I can rest just as well
in a chair.

22:32.316 --> 22:33.282
[ Chuckles ]

22:33.317 --> 22:35.284
Do you like stories?

22:35.319 --> 22:36.285
Oh, good.

22:36.320 --> 22:37.908
You can tell me some.

22:37.942 --> 22:40.048
[ Cellphone chimes ]

22:40.082 --> 22:41.394
Dr. Benson Kwan?

22:41.429 --> 22:42.602
We need to ask you
some questions

22:42.637 --> 22:44.121
about the Alvarez case.

22:44.155 --> 22:45.778
I just got called in for
a consult back in the E.R. --

22:45.812 --> 22:47.711
Your patient tested positive
for fentanyl.

22:47.745 --> 22:49.609
This is now a criminal
investigation involving a minor.

22:49.644 --> 22:51.749
It will only take a couple
minutes of your time.

22:51.784 --> 22:55.926
♪♪

23:04.175 --> 23:07.247
Denise, why are your friends
cutting down all my roses?

23:07.282 --> 23:09.249
Uh,
they're doing what?
[ Gasps ]

23:09.284 --> 23:10.734
Oh, my baby.

23:10.768 --> 23:12.425
Look at you.

23:12.460 --> 23:13.426
Hi, Mom.

23:13.461 --> 23:14.772
Oh.

23:16.464 --> 23:18.293
You are a beauty.

23:19.190 --> 23:21.607
And you are my star.

23:21.641 --> 23:24.472
And, baby girl,
don't you marry Kenneth

23:24.506 --> 23:26.646
if you don't
really love him.

23:26.681 --> 23:30.339
If you love Dewayne
and he sees you for who you are,

23:30.374 --> 23:32.963
don't you walk
down that aisle.

23:32.997 --> 23:36.967
Honey, it's better
to disappoint everybody else

23:37.001 --> 23:40.073
than it is
to disappoint yourself.

23:40.108 --> 23:42.317
And your mama
loves you.

23:42.351 --> 23:44.457
I love you.

23:44.492 --> 23:50.256
♪♪

23:50.290 --> 23:51.844
And the plot thickens.

23:54.605 --> 23:56.745
Man over PA:
Dr. Gear to E.R., stat.

23:56.780 --> 23:59.230
Dr. Gear to E.R., stat.

24:01.232 --> 24:03.338
I asked to stay
while they talked,

24:03.372 --> 24:04.857
but I was shown the door,

24:04.891 --> 24:06.928
so I eavesdropped
on the nurses.

24:06.962 --> 24:09.275
Enzo has fentanyl
in his blood?

24:09.309 --> 24:11.795
I can't answer that 'cause
doctor/patient --

24:11.829 --> 24:14.487
And they think his mother
gave it to him?

24:14.522 --> 24:16.869
Why the hell
would she do that?

24:18.008 --> 24:20.493
You think --
You think they have it wrong?

24:21.805 --> 24:24.117
I can't prove it,

24:24.152 --> 24:27.327
and I also might be partial
to single moms and their sons.

24:27.362 --> 24:30.538
If you think the police
have this wrong,

24:30.572 --> 24:32.471
then you have to fight.

24:32.505 --> 24:35.163
You have to fight like hell
to help her,

24:35.197 --> 24:39.339
or you risk it waking you up
in the night when you're 80.

24:39.374 --> 24:40.513
[ Sighs ]

24:40.548 --> 24:42.308
I just started
my residency here.

24:42.342 --> 24:45.794
When I first started teaching,
there was a young assistant.

24:45.829 --> 24:47.520
Her name was Claire.

24:47.555 --> 24:50.903
She was a bit of an odd duck,
really, kept to herself,

24:50.937 --> 24:53.043
but the kids loved her.

24:53.077 --> 24:55.632
Anyway, she often came
in late and --

24:55.666 --> 24:57.703
and sometimes
had bruises on her face.

24:57.737 --> 25:00.429
So I asked another teacher
about it,

25:00.464 --> 25:04.744
and she said that her husband
was a bigwig alum

25:04.779 --> 25:06.815
who fundraised
for the school.

25:06.850 --> 25:08.990
In other words --
stop asking.

25:09.024 --> 25:13.097
So I did.
I didn't want to lose my job.

25:13.132 --> 25:16.204
A few weeks later,
Claire was dead.

25:16.238 --> 25:20.035
And that'swhat keeps me
up at night.

25:20.070 --> 25:23.832
Not my divorce,
not my old friends dying,

25:23.867 --> 25:26.766
not my failures as a mother,
of which there are many.

25:26.801 --> 25:29.597
No, it's the thought
of that --

25:29.631 --> 25:32.772
that poor young woman
that I didn't fight for.

25:32.807 --> 25:39.330
♪♪

25:40.884 --> 25:43.852
Wait, we're letting them
arrest her?

25:43.887 --> 25:45.095
They're gonna take her
to the station

25:45.129 --> 25:46.648
once she's
medically clear.

25:47.649 --> 25:49.099
Look, we don't have
a choice.

25:49.133 --> 25:51.584
CPS only had more questions
after the interview.

25:51.619 --> 25:53.517
An interview that was
in broken Spanish.

25:54.483 --> 25:56.693
Did they even wait
for an interpreter?

25:56.727 --> 25:58.315
They'll continue
the investigation,

25:58.349 --> 26:00.800
but for now, we need to do
what's best for Enzo.

26:00.835 --> 26:02.284
What,
by splitting him up

26:02.319 --> 26:03.976
with the only person
that cares about him?

26:04.010 --> 26:05.771
I -- [ Sighs ]They are on vacation
from Buenos Aires.

26:05.805 --> 26:07.600
They rented a home here
because Enzo is obsessed

26:07.635 --> 26:09.050
with Mount Rainier
and the Space Needle

26:09.084 --> 26:10.914
since his dad was
from here.

26:10.948 --> 26:13.088
I think the system
is making assumptions

26:13.123 --> 26:16.264
that they wouldn't make
if she was speaking English.

26:16.298 --> 26:18.611
Carmen doesn't even know
what fentanyl is.

26:18.646 --> 26:20.268
If she saw it,
she would think it was candy

26:20.302 --> 26:22.270
because the pills are in bright,
shiny rainbow colors --

26:22.304 --> 26:23.340
Kwan.

26:26.861 --> 26:27.931
Carmen.

26:32.452 --> 26:33.488
No.

26:40.046 --> 26:41.669
Dr. Hunt!

26:44.292 --> 26:45.845
[ Thudding ]

26:45.880 --> 26:47.088
Turbulence shouldn't
last this long.

26:47.122 --> 26:48.537
We should go higher.

26:48.572 --> 26:50.022
Now you're telling the pilots
what to do?

26:50.056 --> 26:51.299
That tracks.

26:51.333 --> 26:53.197
Well, it's, uh,
global warming.

26:53.232 --> 26:55.130
Air currents colliding
at high altitudes,

26:55.165 --> 26:57.616
making turbulence
harder to predict.

26:58.582 --> 27:00.101
In case anyone cares.

27:00.135 --> 27:01.205
Whoa!

27:02.172 --> 27:03.863
You okay?I'm so sorry.
I'm fine.

27:03.898 --> 27:05.554
What else
do you want me to say?

27:05.589 --> 27:06.970
I was in an awful place.

27:07.004 --> 27:08.972
I feel terrible
about the way I treated you.

27:09.006 --> 27:10.456
Do you still stand
by what you said?

27:10.490 --> 27:12.147
I stand by my apology.

27:12.182 --> 27:13.632
Forget the apology,
Amelia.

27:13.666 --> 27:14.978
Do you believe there's truth
to what you said?

27:15.012 --> 27:16.496
I-I-I'll give
my entire salary

27:16.531 --> 27:18.050
to the first person
who switches seats.

27:18.084 --> 27:19.499
Not worth it.

27:19.534 --> 27:21.398
I was harsh,
I was out of line,

27:21.432 --> 27:23.503
but I think there was some truth
to what I said,

27:23.538 --> 27:24.573
and I think
you know it.

27:24.608 --> 27:26.645
You were supposed to
love Maggie,

27:26.679 --> 27:27.853
not compete with her.

27:27.887 --> 27:29.302
You don't know me.
Okay?

27:29.337 --> 27:30.890
You --
You don't have any idea

27:30.925 --> 27:33.306
what I had to overcome
to get here.

27:33.341 --> 27:34.860
The discipline
that it took.

27:34.894 --> 27:36.551
There's not
a single doctor

27:36.585 --> 27:38.484
or even college graduate
in my family,

27:38.518 --> 27:40.555
and now I'm one of the best
heart surgeons in the country.

27:40.589 --> 27:42.971
And I've been called small
and a coward.

27:43.006 --> 27:45.422
And a failure because
my marriage didn't work out.

27:45.456 --> 27:47.079
Because my wife and I
wanted different things.

27:47.113 --> 27:49.668
Because I won't compromise
everything that I've built

27:49.702 --> 27:51.393
by throwing tantrums
at work.

27:51.428 --> 27:53.499
That's not me.
Never gonna happen.

27:53.533 --> 27:54.880
I didn't fail Maggie.

27:54.914 --> 27:56.605
And you know what?
Maggie didn't fail me.

27:56.640 --> 27:57.814
If you think
that I was the problem

27:57.848 --> 27:58.987
and you were in her ear?

27:59.022 --> 28:00.333
You might be
the reason she left!

28:00.368 --> 28:01.576
I was not in her ear!

28:01.610 --> 28:03.164
One day,
we'll all be dead!

28:03.198 --> 28:04.821
Does it have to be
today?

28:04.855 --> 28:07.237
And when that time comes,
when you're in the afterlife,

28:07.271 --> 28:08.445
chilling on a cloud,

28:08.479 --> 28:10.447
will you be proud
of this moment?

28:10.481 --> 28:12.863
Will it have uplifted
your souls?

28:12.898 --> 28:15.624
Or will you realize that
you've wasted precious life

28:15.659 --> 28:17.281
with petty arguments?

28:17.316 --> 28:19.042
Will it fill you
with pride?

28:19.076 --> 28:21.044
Or shame and regret?

28:21.078 --> 28:24.185
Um [clears throat]
my wife has been hitting

28:24.219 --> 28:26.463
the medical marijuana
pretty hard lately.

28:26.497 --> 28:28.051
[ Loud thud ]
Whoa!

28:28.085 --> 28:29.466
Okay, okay, okay.
Oh!

28:29.500 --> 28:31.330
Pilot: Hang on, folks.
It's getting bumpy.

28:37.405 --> 28:39.718
This is not how
I'm supposed to die!

28:39.752 --> 28:43.135
I have cancer, damn it!
That's how I'm gonna die!

28:43.169 --> 28:45.585
Catherine, we're not dying!
Take my hand.

28:45.620 --> 28:47.484
We're going down, baby!

28:47.518 --> 28:50.107
This is why people
fly commercial!

28:50.142 --> 28:51.730
It feels like
we're plummeting.

28:51.764 --> 28:53.870
We are!I can't die,
I'm a mom.

28:53.904 --> 28:55.664
I can't die,
I can't die --

28:55.699 --> 28:58.115
Amelia,
give me your hand.

28:58.150 --> 29:00.221
Oh,
I should have retired!

29:00.255 --> 29:02.637
Why, God?!

29:03.811 --> 29:05.295
Give me that.

29:05.329 --> 29:06.745
Bailey:
Oh, hell, no.

29:06.779 --> 29:11.819
♪♪

29:11.853 --> 29:13.337
Oh, geez.

29:15.339 --> 29:17.445
Pilot: I am so sorry, folks.
That was rough.

29:17.479 --> 29:18.964
We hit an unexpected
wind shear,

29:18.998 --> 29:20.828
but we are through it,
and I hope everyone's okay.

29:20.862 --> 29:22.450
We're expecting smooth skies

29:22.484 --> 29:23.969
for the remainder
of the flight.Oh, my God.

29:24.003 --> 29:27.282
[ Laughs ]

29:34.151 --> 29:35.912
Woman over PA: Dr. Davis
to Labor and Delivery.

29:35.946 --> 29:38.742
Dr. Megan Davis
to Labor and Delivery.

29:41.987 --> 29:43.712
[ Clears throat ]

29:43.747 --> 29:45.922
Am I fired?

29:45.956 --> 29:49.580
As much as I'd like to think
I have firing power, I do not.

29:50.581 --> 29:52.342
[ Sighs ]

29:52.376 --> 29:54.654
I grew up
with a single mom.

29:54.689 --> 29:56.449
Yeah, I did, too.

29:56.484 --> 30:00.937
And most of the time,
I find it to be a strength.

30:00.971 --> 30:04.699
It's helped with my compassion,
patience, empathy,

30:04.733 --> 30:07.702
but not all single moms
are like ours.

30:07.736 --> 30:11.430
So we have to follow
the protocols...

30:12.500 --> 30:14.019
...as hard as it is.

30:15.434 --> 30:17.505
[ Clears throat ]

30:18.886 --> 30:20.957
Police searched
their rental.

30:20.991 --> 30:22.406
In a bedside drawer,
they found

30:22.441 --> 30:24.961
a baggie of weed gummies
and rainbow fentanyl.

30:24.995 --> 30:27.480
They confirmed that they were
left by the previous occupants.

30:27.515 --> 30:29.655
For a child to find.Mm-hmm.

30:29.689 --> 30:33.590
Dr. Kwan,
you fought the good fight --

30:33.624 --> 30:35.005
and you won.

30:36.075 --> 30:37.490
What do I do
with the rage?

30:37.525 --> 30:39.320
[ Sighs ]

30:39.354 --> 30:41.770
That is a question
for the ages in this job.

30:43.013 --> 30:45.429
Meantime, why don't you
take Carmen inside

30:45.464 --> 30:47.880
to go see her son,
okay?

30:47.915 --> 30:48.985
Yeah.

30:49.019 --> 30:53.092
♪♪

30:53.127 --> 30:54.783
Enzo.

30:54.818 --> 30:56.475
Enzo: Mom?

30:57.476 --> 30:58.580
Estoy aquí.

31:00.651 --> 31:02.688
Sam: What are you doing
over there?

31:02.722 --> 31:05.173
I'm checking
your chest tube.

31:05.208 --> 31:06.899
Wow. Okay.

31:06.934 --> 31:08.521
I don't usually like to move
this fast, but if you insist.

31:08.556 --> 31:09.626
[ Chuckles ]

31:09.660 --> 31:11.973
I don't believe that
for a second.

31:12.940 --> 31:14.286
The tube looks good.

31:14.320 --> 31:16.357
They'll probably remove it
in a couple of days.

31:16.391 --> 31:17.599
Signal is strong.

31:18.842 --> 31:20.637
So, when they ask...

31:20.671 --> 31:21.914
we can tell our kids

31:21.949 --> 31:24.261
that this was
our first date, right?

31:24.296 --> 31:25.987
[ Chuckles ]

31:33.961 --> 31:36.308
How's his H&H and INR?

31:36.342 --> 31:37.654
Uh, stable.

31:38.862 --> 31:41.830
Then I guess
I'll leave you to it.

31:41.865 --> 31:45.524
Link, is there something
that you need to say to me?

31:47.353 --> 31:48.492
[ Sighs ]

31:48.527 --> 31:49.838
I just...

31:51.116 --> 31:52.496
You're...

31:54.153 --> 31:55.672
...one of his doctors.

31:55.706 --> 31:57.122
Oh, my God.

31:57.156 --> 31:58.433
Link.

31:58.468 --> 32:00.263
You slept with an intern.

32:00.297 --> 32:01.643
Did I judge you?

32:01.678 --> 32:03.956
[ Wildes' "Lightly" plays ]

32:03.991 --> 32:08.443
♪ I think I see it,
on the horizon ♪

32:08.478 --> 32:11.412
♪ Now I feel it

32:11.446 --> 32:15.588
♪ And I'm alive,
but am I breathing? ♪

32:15.623 --> 32:18.419
♪ Fill my lungs
so I can scream it ♪

32:18.453 --> 32:19.627
Hey.

32:19.661 --> 32:21.940
♪ When I cried on the floor...

32:21.974 --> 32:23.942
It might not be
the one you ordered,

32:23.976 --> 32:25.184
but it's made with love,

32:25.219 --> 32:26.289
from all
your neighbors' houses.

32:26.323 --> 32:27.531
Ow, ow!
Oh, sorry!

32:27.566 --> 32:28.705
No, it's okay.
Thorns?

32:28.739 --> 32:29.948
Ah.

32:29.982 --> 32:31.777
Oh, my God.
You're bleeding on your dress.

32:31.811 --> 32:32.778
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God, help.

32:32.812 --> 32:34.297
Uh...

32:34.331 --> 32:35.988
Uh, Mr. Griffith,
may I?

32:36.023 --> 32:38.853
I'm so sorry.You can just call me
Dewayne.

32:38.887 --> 32:39.958
It's not coming out.Here, let's just go.

32:39.992 --> 32:41.442
Okay. Okay.

32:41.476 --> 32:43.375
We're gonna take
this...

32:43.409 --> 32:44.790
put it through that.

32:44.824 --> 32:47.172
Okay, hold your bouquet
right there.

32:47.206 --> 32:48.276
You can't see
the blood.

32:48.311 --> 32:49.450
Okay.
There.

32:49.484 --> 32:51.900
You look beautiful.
Thank you.

32:51.935 --> 32:53.040
Dewayne:
It's all good.

32:53.074 --> 32:54.041
It's okay, baby.

32:54.075 --> 32:55.490
Here we go.

32:55.525 --> 32:57.285
♪ Maybe I love how I feel
in the wind ♪

32:57.320 --> 32:58.286
♪ I'm the breeze

32:58.321 --> 33:00.875
♪ So light

33:02.428 --> 33:09.021
♪ I'm li-i-i-i-i-i-i-ght

33:09.056 --> 33:10.816
[ Chuckles ]

33:10.850 --> 33:16.856
♪ I'm li-i-i-i-i-i-i-ght

33:19.169 --> 33:21.482
♪ Can you feel it?

33:21.516 --> 33:24.657
♪ Close to you?

33:24.692 --> 33:29.007
Dad, was Mom engaged
to someone else before you?

33:29.041 --> 33:31.250
Baby, why would you --Just tell me
the truth, please.

33:31.285 --> 33:37.291
♪♪

33:39.189 --> 33:40.604
[ Clears throat ]

33:40.639 --> 33:44.436
I have n-never seen
two people more in love.

33:44.470 --> 33:46.093
She met me two months

33:46.127 --> 33:48.923
before they were
supposed to get married.

33:48.957 --> 33:51.098
And she called off
the wedding last minute?

33:51.132 --> 33:55.447
Baby, your mother always made
life up as she went along.

33:55.481 --> 34:01.487
♪ I'm li-i-i-i-i-i-i-ght

34:04.145 --> 34:10.255
♪ I'm li-i-i-i-i-i-i-ght

34:14.431 --> 34:17.538
You and I are
quite the dynamic duo.

34:17.572 --> 34:19.091
[ Chuckles ]

34:19.126 --> 34:21.128
Oh, come on.
I helped a little bit.

34:21.161 --> 34:22.543
I sat with the boy.

34:22.577 --> 34:24.614
I talked
about the Beatles.
Mm.

34:24.648 --> 34:26.822
Can you guess what
his favorite song is?

34:28.135 --> 34:29.101
"Yellow Submarine"?

34:29.136 --> 34:30.378
How did you know?

34:30.413 --> 34:33.208
Ah.
All kids like it.

34:33.243 --> 34:35.659
I can see why Jules
is falling for you.

34:35.694 --> 34:37.109
Ah, falling for me?

34:37.143 --> 34:40.216
Uh, yeah, she barely
speaks to me.

34:40.250 --> 34:42.839
She's a wounded bird
with a mass--

34:42.873 --> 34:43.840
with a ma--

34:43.873 --> 34:46.670
massive h-- heart.

34:46.705 --> 34:48.672
M-Maxine?
The two of --
The two of you --

34:48.706 --> 34:49.672
Maxine!

34:49.708 --> 34:50.985
[ Gasping ]

34:51.018 --> 34:52.297
I need some help
in here!

34:52.331 --> 34:56.577
[ Gasping ]

34:56.610 --> 34:58.337
It's okay,
it's okay, it's okay.

35:01.271 --> 35:02.790
Code Blue!
I need a crash cart!

35:02.824 --> 35:03.860
Woman:
Code Blue, 4th floor.

35:03.894 --> 35:05.275
Hold on, Maxine.
Hold on.

35:05.310 --> 35:07.415
She has
a DNR and DNI.

35:07.450 --> 35:09.314
No, she was fine.
She was just talking.

35:09.348 --> 35:11.971
Dr. Kwan, we're not supposed to
do anything. It's in her chart.

35:12.006 --> 35:13.594
Get me an intubation tray
so I can save her life!

35:13.628 --> 35:14.664
Dr. Kwan!

35:14.698 --> 35:16.044
Code Blue, 4th floor.Go!

35:16.079 --> 35:17.460
Neuro ICU.

35:17.494 --> 35:18.461
Code Blue, 4th floor,
Neuro ICU.

35:18.495 --> 35:19.703
It's okay.
Here we go.

35:26.917 --> 35:30.266
Woman over PA: Dr. Sellers,
Dr. Mari Sellers 4619.

35:30.300 --> 35:34.649
Dr. Mari Sellers 4619.

35:34.684 --> 35:36.686
[ Sighs ]

35:37.549 --> 35:39.447
Hey.

35:39.482 --> 35:40.690
You need to eat.

35:40.724 --> 35:42.519
[ Sighs ]
It hurts when I chew.

35:42.554 --> 35:44.659
Yeah, I thought you might
say that, so...

35:44.694 --> 35:46.040
Oh.

35:48.318 --> 35:50.182
Mm.

35:50.217 --> 35:51.321
Hey.

35:51.356 --> 35:52.667
You always
take care of me.

35:52.702 --> 35:55.325
Yep, I will always
take care of you.

35:57.258 --> 35:59.018
Drink the whole thing.

35:59.053 --> 36:00.744
Bossy.
[ Chuckles ]

36:02.056 --> 36:04.679
Meredith: It has been proven
that what you believe

36:04.714 --> 36:07.993
can sometimes determine
the state of your health.

36:08.027 --> 36:10.409
Catherine, slow down!

36:10.444 --> 36:12.687
So it goes to follow
that it can also

36:12.722 --> 36:15.414
sometimes determine
the state of your life.

36:15.449 --> 36:18.314
♪ ...scared of the darkness

36:18.348 --> 36:20.488
[ Sighs ]

36:20.523 --> 36:22.490
Marsh,
are you coming?

36:22.525 --> 36:25.044
Marsh?
We're headed to the hotel.

36:25.079 --> 36:28.116
Yeah, I-I'll -- I'll meet up
with you guys later.

36:28.151 --> 36:30.188
There's, uh,
something I need to do.

36:30.222 --> 36:32.328
♪ Eyes open wide

36:32.362 --> 36:34.122
Uh, Ben?
Call me back.

36:34.157 --> 36:35.676
We just landed.

36:35.710 --> 36:37.747
I'm checking on you
and the kids.

36:37.781 --> 36:39.335
Okay, love you.
Bye.

36:39.369 --> 36:42.027
And what you believe
can change on a dime.

36:42.061 --> 36:43.201
♪ To get there

36:43.235 --> 36:45.444
[ Sighs ]

36:45.479 --> 36:46.583
♪ We walk the line

36:46.618 --> 36:47.619
What you believe is right...

36:47.653 --> 36:49.586
Give me
the intubation tray.

36:49.621 --> 36:50.967
Bring in the cart!

36:51.001 --> 36:51.968
...what you believe is wrong...

36:52.002 --> 36:54.039
♪ We look for signs

36:54.073 --> 36:59.631
♪ After all we find,
it takes time ♪

36:59.665 --> 37:00.942
...what you believe you want...

37:00.977 --> 37:02.737
♪ It takes time

37:02.772 --> 37:06.914
♪ For us to feel

37:06.948 --> 37:08.467
♪ To know what's real

37:08.502 --> 37:10.745
...what you believe you need...

37:10.780 --> 37:13.127
♪ For hearts to heal

37:13.161 --> 37:14.611
Oh, my gosh.
What did you do?

37:14.646 --> 37:16.924
Help me.
Do not intubate!

37:16.958 --> 37:18.097
That's what she wanted!

37:18.132 --> 37:19.582
She explicitly
did not want

37:19.616 --> 37:20.928
to be on a machine
for the rest of her life.

37:20.962 --> 37:22.378
She was just talking,

37:22.412 --> 37:24.587
and she was helping me
with a patient and laughing.

37:24.621 --> 37:26.278
Help me fight
to get her back.

37:26.313 --> 37:27.417
She dropped a lung.

37:27.452 --> 37:28.418
Then let's put in
a chest tube.

37:28.453 --> 37:29.833
Kwan, you need to stop.

37:29.868 --> 37:31.387
I already intubated her!
We can't half-save her!

37:31.421 --> 37:32.491
Page Dr. Bailey.

37:32.526 --> 37:33.630
She's on her way
to Boston.

37:33.665 --> 37:36.254
[ Scoffs ]

37:36.288 --> 37:38.601
...what you believe you
are capable of doing...

37:38.635 --> 37:40.292
Chest tube tray.

37:42.363 --> 37:44.434
...what you believe
is a sign...

37:44.469 --> 37:49.577
♪♪

37:49.612 --> 37:51.338
You see her, too,
right?

37:51.372 --> 37:53.995
Most definitely.

37:54.030 --> 37:56.274
♪ Find who we are

37:56.308 --> 37:58.206
♪ Find who we are

37:58.241 --> 38:00.416
♪ Find who we are

38:00.450 --> 38:02.521
♪ Find who we are

